<br>
My LDON parties will be Open Roll on all non no drop items.  A player may override the open roll if they see an item they need, but they must put up the item they are replacing for roll.  Example. If a AC 50 hand item drops, it is open roll, but Powpow says &quot;hey, I can use that&quot;. Powpow must put up his current hands for roll to the others who helped get it.  If Powpow's hands are no drop, he must win the roll fair and square.<br>
<br>
On LDON raids, there will be 3 different loot tables/lists.  1 - Augments. 2 - Named mob loot. 3 - other loot like gems and smaller items.  If you roll and win for one of these, you must pass on the same type of item if it comes up again until everyone has one.  If a + str augment drops, Powpow may roll for it.  Sele as a chanter does not really need it and would not roll. If Pow wins, the next augment that comes up could be a +dex which he could also use, but he must pass.  If a blue diamond drops, Pow is eligable to roll and win because its on a different loot table/list.<br>
<br>
If a mob drops multiple items to roll on, or loot is being split at the end of a raid, each item will get its own roll. We will not roll once and let players who get the highest select what they get from what is left.<br>
<br>
Of course with my BBSco crew, I would use NBG because I want my guildies to get great gear.<br>
<br>
The story that brought this up was a LDON I did with some people who must have bought their accouns because they had no idea what they were doing.  We killed a named mob and a great robe dropped.  We all rolled when told to. I won with a 947. I never get higher than 947.  I won. WOOT.  Well then someone said &quot;maybe the wizzy needs it&quot;. The wizzy linked his item and sure enough, he did. They told me to give it to the wizzy.  I did but asked that the wizzy give up his current robe for roll.  No answer. No robe to me.  Then we rolled on a diamond. Everyone re-rolled.  The wizzy won!  They gratz'd him. I said &quot;wait a minute&quot; adn they gave me the diamond since I had the second highest roll this time.  I was a little ticked because the loot rules were not stated up front, they said to roll greed on it, and then the wizzy was getting all the loot =).  <br>
<br>
I love loot. It floats my boat.<br>
<br>
Pow <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/bblackburrowstoutco13800.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dillesgeleuze>Dilles Geleuze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/30/03 11:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=391.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mysite.verizon.net/vze43w7b/dillesblu.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take on loot policies</span><hr size=1> sounds good to me, pow. and i would add that if at the end of a raid or ldon we have 2 of the same item (blue diamonds, for ex), everyone should roll once and the double item should go to 2 highest. thats for when theres a ML (main looter). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/bblackburrowstoutco13800.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dankpelt>DankPelt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/1/03 10:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=391.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take on loot policies</span><hr size=1> The only thing that I would add is that if there is a ML in the group, I think it's a bit silly to roll on non-quest gems. Everyone in the group contributed, and in the end... everyone gets a little more plat. Seems to work good.<br>
